In-class Activity: Hurricane Tracks

Baby Names

library("tidyverse")

theme_set(theme_minimal())
katrina <- filter(storms, name == "Katrina" & year == 2005)

Basic bubble chart

ggplot(katrina, aes(x = long, y = lat, size = wind)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.75) +
  coord_equal()

ggplot(katrina, aes(x = long, y = lat, size = wind, color = wind)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.75) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "cividis") +
  coord_equal()

Combine color bar with legend

ggplot(katrina, aes(x = long, y = lat, size = wind, color = wind)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.75) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "cividis") +
  coord_equal() +
  guides(color = guide_legend())

Map!

library("rnaturalearth")

world <- ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf")

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = world) +
  geom_point(data = katrina, aes(x = long, y = lat, size = wind, color = wind),
             alpha = 0.75) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "cividis") +
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-102, -70), ylim = c(10, 38)) +
  guides(color = guide_legend())

A few minor tweaks to the theme to make a fancy, publication-quality map.

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = world, fill = "antiquewhite1") +
  geom_point(data = katrina,
             aes(x = long, y = lat, size = wind, color = wind),
             alpha = 0.75) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "cividis") +
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-102, -70), ylim = c(10, 38), expand = FALSE) +
  guides(color = guide_legend()) +
  labs(x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude") +
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = gray(0.5),
                                        linetype = "dashed",
                                        size = 0.5),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = "aliceblue"),
        panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA))
